The White House announced Monday that Michael Flynn has resigned as President Donald Trump&#8217;s national security advisor, amid escalating controversy over his contacts with Moscow.In his formal resignation letter, Flynn acknowledged that in the period leading up to Trump&#8217;s inauguration: &#8220;I inadvertently briefed the vice president-elect and others with incomplete information regarding my phone calls with the Russian ambassador.&#8221;Trump has named retired lieutenant general Joseph Kellogg, who was serving as a director on the Joint Chiefs of Staff, as acting national security advisor, the White House said.-AFP